                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/286.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tampico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-06-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 20, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to telegram June 17 relative to oil companies tendering payment of bar
                    taxes to local authorities in Constitutionalist currency, basing such action
                    upon decree No. 21, dated Nogales, February 28, 1914, now advise Department
                    local authorities only accepted first payment tendered subject to instructions
                    to be requested of Carranza, and now refuse to accept others and are demanding
                    such payments to be made in gold.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Miller</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
